{
  "info": {
    "name": "Help PR — Order refunds",
    "description": "**/api/refund** — Order refund APIs (list, eligible orders, detail, create).\n\n**Doc:** `docs/REFUND_API.md` (API reference + create body mapping)\n**Frontend:** `docs/REFUND_FRONTEND.md`\n\n**Access:** Super admin (5) & staff (6); franchise admin (1) & employee (3). Partner (2) & customer (4) → 403.\n\n**Flow (manual):** 1 Login → 2 Eligible orders → 4 Create → 1 Get all → 3 Get by id\n**Flow (Razorpay):** 2 Eligible orders (check `razorpay_refundable_amount`) → **4b Create — Razorpay refund**\n\n**Variables:** `orderId` from eligible-orders `_id`; `refundMongoId` from getAll/create `data._id`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:5001" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "franchiseId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "orderId", "value": "", "description": "Order Mongo _id from eligible-orders (for create)" },
    { "key": "refundMongoId", "value": "", "description": "order_refund document _id (for getById)" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Get all — refund list",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "if (json.success && json.data?.records?.length) {",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refundMongoId', json.data.records[0]._id);",
              "  console.log('Set refundMongoId:', json.data.records[0]._id);",
              "}",
              "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}", "type": "text" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/refund/getAll?page=1&limit=10&order_id=&user_name=&from_date=&to_date=&franchise_id={{franchiseId}}&sort_by=refund_date&sort_order=desc",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "refund", "getAll"],
          "query": [
            { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
            { "key": "limit", "value": "10", "description": "Max 100" },
            { "key": "order_id", "value": "", "description": "Search unique_id or Mongo ObjectId" },
            { "key": "user_name", "value": "" },
            { "key": "from_date", "value": "", "description": "Filter refund_date (optional)" },
            { "key": "to_date", "value": "", "description": "Filter refund_date (optional)" },
            { "key": "franchise_id", "value": "{{franchiseId}}" },
            { "key": "sort_by", "value": "refund_date", "description": "order_id | user_name | refund_date | refund_amount" },
            { "key": "sort_order", "value": "desc" }
          ]
        },
        "description": "**GET /api/refund/getAll** — Refund history.\n\nSee `docs/REFUND_API.md` §1.\n\nTest script sets `refundMongoId` from first record."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Eligible orders — create picker",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "if (json.success && json.data?.records?.length) {",
              "  const row = json.data.records[0];",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('orderId', row._id);",
              "  console.log('Set orderId:', row._id, 'refundable:', row.refundable_amount ?? row.user_paid, 'razorpay:', row.razorpay_refundable_amount);",
              "}",
              "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}", "type": "text" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/refund/eligible-orders?page=1&limit=10&order_id=&user_name=&franchise_id={{franchiseId}}&sort_by=order_id&sort_order=asc",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "refund", "eligible-orders"],
          "query": [
            { "key": "page", "value": "1" },
            { "key": "limit", "value": "10" },
            { "key": "order_id", "value": "" },
            { "key": "user_name", "value": "" },
            { "key": "franchise_id", "value": "{{franchiseId}}" },
            { "key": "sort_by", "value": "order_id" },
            { "key": "sort_order", "value": "asc" }
          ]
        },
        "description": "**GET /api/refund/eligible-orders** — Orders with refundable balance.\n\nSee `docs/REFUND_API.md` §2.\n\n`razorpay_refundable_amount` = max refundable via Razorpay API. `partner_payable_amount` + `admin_payable_amount` = `refundable_amount`."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Get by id — refund detail",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}", "type": "text" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/refund/getById/{{refundMongoId}}",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "refund", "getById", "{{refundMongoId}}"]
        },
        "description": "**GET /api/refund/getById/:id** — `:id` = refund Mongo `_id` (`refundMongoId`).\n\nSee `docs/REFUND_API.md` §3."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Create — record refund",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "if (json.success && json.data?._id) {",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refundMongoId', json.data._id);",
              "  console.log('Created refund:', json.data._id);",
              "}",
              "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}", "type": "text" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"order_id\": \"{{orderId}}\",\n  \"refund_amount\": 1000,\n  \"from_admin_commission\": 200,\n  \"from_partner_wallet\": 800,\n  \"date\": \"2026-05-15T10:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"notes\": \"Refund via Postman\",\n  \"payment_method\": \"refund\",\n  \"transaction_reference\": \"\"\n}",
          "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/refund/create",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "refund", "create"]
        },
        "description": "**POST /api/refund/create** — Manual ledger refund (cash/bank already returned offline).\n\nSee `docs/REFUND_API.md` §4."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4b. Create — Razorpay refund (admin)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const json = pm.response.json();",
              "if (json.success && json.data?._id) {",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refundMongoId', json.data._id);",
              "  console.log('Razorpay refund:', json.data._id, json.data.razorpay_refund_details);",
              "}",
              "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
              "pm.test('Razorpay channel', () => pm.expect(json.data?.refund_channel).to.eql('razorpay'));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}", "type": "text" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json", "type": "text" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"order_id\": \"{{orderId}}\",\n  \"refund_amount\": 1000,\n  \"from_admin_commission\": 1000,\n  \"from_partner_wallet\": 0,\n  \"date\": \"2026-06-20T10:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"notes\": \"Razorpay refund via Postman\",\n  \"refund_via_razorpay\": true\n}",
          "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/refund/create",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "refund", "create"]
        },
        "description": "**POST /api/refund/create** with `refund_via_razorpay: true`.\n\n**Admin only** (same JWT as other refund routes). Calls Razorpay Refund API, then records `order_refund` + ledger.\n\n**Prerequisites:** Order paid online (Razorpay); `refund_amount` ≤ `razorpay_refundable_amount` from **2. Eligible orders**.\n\n**Response:** `refund_channel: razorpay`, `razorpay_refund_details[].razorpay_refund_id` (`rfnd_xxx`)."
      }
    }
  ]
}
